        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 1:11PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 111 PM EDT, a rapidly developing thunderstorm was located over
Wright-Patterson Afb, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation.

Locations impacted include...
Green Meadows, Medway, Donnelsville, Springfield Municipal Airport,
Hustead, Enon, Holiday Valley, Huber Heights, Snyderville, Crystal
Lakes, Wright-Patterson Afb, Fairborn, Park Layne, Yellow Springs,
Riverside, Beavercreek, Springfield, and Dayton.

This includes I-70 in Ohio between mile markers 38 and 53.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM EDT for
west central Ohio.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
